+===============================================================================
+Lenovo Legion Pro 7 16IAX10H - AW88399 HDA Side-Codec Audio Driver
+Linux 7.0+ Module Load Order and Configuration
+===============================================================================
+
+CRITICAL ISSUE - Module Load Order
+===================================
+
+The Lenovo Legion Pro 7 16IAX10H uses the Awinic AW88399 smart amplifier 
+connected as an HDA side codec to the Realtek ALC287 codec.
+
+Linux 7.0+ enforces stricter ACPI device driver probing, which means both:
+  * snd_soc_aw88399 (SOC/SSP-based driver)
+  * snd_hda_scodec_aw88399_i2c (HDA side-codec driver)
+
+Cannot bind to the same device simultaneously. The HDA driver MUST probe first.
+
+
+RECOMMENDED KERNEL CONFIGURATION
+==================================
+
+For Lenovo Legion Pro 7 16IAX10H:
+
+  CONFIG_SND_HDA_INTEL=y                    # Built-in
+  CONFIG_SND_HDA_CODEC_REALTEK=y            # Built-in
+  CONFIG_SND_HDA_SCODEC_AW88399=m           # As module
+  CONFIG_SND_HDA_SCODEC_AW88399_I2C=m       # As module
+  CONFIG_SND_SOC_AW88399=m                  # As module (optional)
+
+
+AUTOMATIC MODULE LOADING (/etc/modprobe.d/)
+=============================================
+
+Create a file: /etc/modprobe.d/aw88399-load-order.conf
+
+---CUT HERE---
+# Force HDA AW88399 driver to load before SOC driver
+# This prevents device binding conflicts on Linux 7.0+
+
+# Load HDA support first
+softdep snd_hda_intel pre: snd_hda_scodec_aw88399
+softdep snd_hda_scodec_aw88399_i2c pre: snd_hda_intel
+
+# Prevent SOC AW88399 from interfering
+install snd_soc_aw88399 /bin/true
+
+# Optional: Automatically load HDA AW88399 when HDA is loaded
+softdep snd_hda_intel post: snd_hda_scodec_aw88399_i2c
+---CUT HERE---
+
+
+MANUAL MODULE LOADING
+=======================
+
+For manual control, load modules in this specific order:
+
+  1. modprobe snd_hda_intel
+  2. modprobe snd_hda_scodec_aw88399
+  3. modprobe snd_hda_scodec_aw88399_i2c
+
+Do NOT load snd_soc_aw88399 if using HDA mode.
+
+
+TROUBLESHOOTING
+================
+
+1. Check module loading order:
+   lsmod | grep aw88399
+   lsmod | grep snd_hda
+
+2. View device binding status:
+   cat /proc/asound/cards
+   cat /proc/asound/pcm
+
+3. Check for binding conflicts in dmesg:
+   dmesg | grep -i "aw88399\|AW88399\|AWDZ8399"
+
+4. Force HDA driver binding (if SOC driver bound first):
+   echo "i2c-AWDZ8399:00" > /sys/bus/i2c/drivers/aw88399-hda/bind
+
+5. Audio not working? Check audio output:
+   aplay -l
+   speaker-test -c 2 -l
+
+
+KERNEL BOOT PARAMETERS
+========================
+
+Add to kernel command line for debugging:
+  hda_model=legionpro7 snd_hda.dev_indent=1
+
+For verbose output:
+  loglevel=8 snd.debug=1